The paper focuses on graph representation learning using graph neural networks, which is a popular topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of unsupervised learning and mutual information maximization is also a common technique in the field of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
